Not your average university – who are we? \xa0


RMIT Online, a subsidiary of RMIT University is an exciting ‘startup’ team dedicated to building a “Community of lifelong learners, successfully navigating the world of work”. We’re small, nimble, fast-paced and working on really exciting futuristic things.


We were created to leverage disruptive innovation in the higher education sector in key local and international markets. With student experience at the forefront of our design, we strive to build world-class online learning experiences with our leading industry partners. And we have a bit of fun along the way.


Sounds great! Tell me about the role \xa0


We are looking for an energetic, customer-focused high achiever to join our fast-moving team. You’ll play a key role in coordinating all the bits and pieces of an education ecosystem for delivery of a seamless and highly satisfying student experience!


Think of it as the conductor of an orchestra, bringing together delivery elements - such as mentors, student support, course design - at the right time. This role is critical to the success of both the mentor’s and student’s experience to ensure the course experience runs smoothly.


You’ll support students and mentors during the course delivery, acting as the RMIT ‘face’ of the course, a triage point to ensure a great student and teacher experience. More specifically:


  • Ensure course set up and readiness before opening courses for orientation and go-live,
  • Triage student and mentor issues, fostering a virtual team across marketing, student support, teaching & learning, course design and technology to resolve issues
  • Track student behaviour around key activities, such as webinars, booking assessments and completing assessments, developing insights and making recommendations where necessary about changes into all elements of the course/course delivery
  • Monitor student and mentors during course delivery activities to engage with students and mentors at risk
  • Ensure completion of student and mentor feedback surveys, consolidating the insights and findings, and feeding back to the virtual course team for future improvements


Let’s talk about you


If you love to achieve through others, can diagnose problems and know who to bring to the table to address them, you’ll flourish in this role. You’ll have community management experience, with strong mentoring and facilitation ability and capacity to provide responsive, customer centred experiences.


With a strong administration and customer service focused background, you're highly organised, well spoken, articulate and can calmly juggle multiple priorities at once, whilst identifying improvement opportunities.


Your excellent communication and interpersonal skills will help you drive and support learning engagement and interaction. \xa0Ability to engage and navigate communication and learning technologies (e.g., Learning Management Systems, Slack, etc.) will be a strong advantage.\xa0

\xa0

You must have an interest in education, a passion for cool tech and grace under pressure!


Ticking your boxes? \xa0


Send us your CV now along with a brief cover letter\xa0telling us about:

  • Who you are and why you want to work with us
  • The most recent LMS you've used; and

Need more convincing?


You’ll be stepping into our brand-new offices in the heart of the CBD, surrounded by a beautifully buzzing team of high achievers who are passionate, friendly and non-boring types.


Some of our benefits include breakfast daily, professional development opportunities, casual dress code, lots of social activities including Friday night drinks, monthly birthday cakes, and more!


You can read more about us here: https://learn.rmitonline.edu.au/
